  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">This fragment consists of the bottom half of the last page of a letter by Lucretia Mott to Maria Weston Chapman. Lucretia Mott tells about a visit to see Harriet Martineau, who has been ill. Martineau is &quot;very cheerful &amp; appears resigned to her fate whatever that may be---an operation may effect a cure &amp; may take her life---she anticipates the latter as a philosopher &amp; as a Christian.&quot;</subfield>
